Class QosTimeliness

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.thomsonreuters.upa.codec.QosTimeliness

extends java.lang.Object
    Quality Timeliness enumerations describe the age of the data.

    • Field Detail

      • UNSPECIFIED

        public static final int UNSPECIFIED
        timeliness is unspecified. Typically used by QoS initialization methods and not intended to be encoded or decoded.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • REALTIME

        public static final int REALTIME
        timeliness is Real Time: data is updated as soon as new data becomes available. This is the highest-quality timeliness value. Real Time in conjunction with a rate of QosRates.TICK_BY_TICK is the best overall QoS.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • DELAYED_UNKNOWN

        public static final int DELAYED_UNKNOWN
        timeliness is delayed, though the amount of delay is unknown. This is a lower quality than REALTIME and might be worse than DELAYED (in which case the delay is known).
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • DELAYED

        public static final int DELAYED
        timeliness is delayed and the amount of delay is provided in Qos.timeInfo(). This is lower quality than REALTIME and might be better than DELAYED_UNKNOWN.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values
